My goal this week was to run run the fngs_pipeline on the SWU_1 dataset and then generate a series of figures and statistics based on the results produced by the pipeline. Below, I explain the three main tasks that I completed after running the pipeline.

  1. For each subject, I produced a Time vs Intensity plot that shows the intensities of all voxels in the subject at each of the 240 timestamps. These figures provide an easy way to sanity check that the pipeline is producing realistic results. In order to generate the graphs, I used the following code in R:
library(reshape2)

dir <- "C:/Users/Tanay Agarwal/Desktop/College Classes/NeuroData 1/Deliverables 10-5/desikan_2mm/"
dir2 <- "C:/Users/Tanay Agarwal/Desktop/College Classes/NeuroData 1/Deliverables 10-5/Intensity_plots/"

for (i in 0027203:0027203) {
  for (session in 1:3) {
    subject <- paste(c("00", i), collapse = "")
    fileName <- paste(c("SWU_1", subject, session, "rest_desikan_2mm"), collapse = "_")
    fileNameCSV <- paste(c(fileName, ".csv"), collapse = "")
    input <- paste(c(dir, fileNameCSV), collapse = "")
    
    ts <- read.csv(input, sep = " ", header = FALSE)
    ts <- melt(ts)
    ts$variable = as.numeric(ts$variable)
    library(ggplot2)
    g <- ggplot(ts, aes(variable, value, color = variable)) + geom_line(color = "red")+labs(x="Time", y="Intensity")
    g <- g + scale_x_continuous("Time") + scale_y_continuous("Intensity")
    
    fileNamePNG <- paste(c(fileName, ".png"), collapse = "")
    ggsave(filename = fileNamePNG, plot = g, path = dir2)
  }
}
